    • Method Detail

      • DeleteCartonContinue

        boolean DeleteCartonContinue(com.yantra.shared.ycp.YFSContext env,
                             java.lang.String s)
                      throws com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSUserExitException

        The deleteCartonContinue method of YCSdeleteCartonUserExit user exit is called by the removeContainerManifest API before deleting carton on the YCS side. If you are extending the system you can use this user exit for deciding whether the rest of YCS deleteCarton method that calls appropriate carrier servers (FEDX/AIRB/UPS) should be executed or not.

        To code custom user exits, implement the method in this interface. The system calls the method in your class. If this method gives any exception, the current transaction is rolled back.


        Related Yantra Documents
        Input XML Input DTD

        Pre-conditions: This user exit is called unconditionally.

        Parameters:
        env - Required. Environment handle returned by the createEnvironment API. This is required for the user exit to raise errors and access environment information.
        s - Required. For more information, see the associated input xml files.


        Returns:
        boolean. For details on the output, refer to the associated output files.


        Throws:
        com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSUserExitException - This exception is thrown whenever system errors that the application cannot handle are encountered. The transaction is aborted and changes are rolled back.


      • DeleteCarton

        java.lang.String DeleteCarton(com.yantra.shared.ycp.YFSContext env,
                              java.lang.String s)
                       throws com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSUserExitException

        The deleteCarton method of YCSdeleteCartonUserExit user exit is called by the removeContainerFromManifest API before deleting carton on the YCS side. If you are extending the system you can use this user exit method for deleting carton on YCS side.

        To code custom user exits, implement the method in this interface. The system calls the method in your class. If this method gives any exception, the current transaction is rolled back.


        Related Yantra Documents
        Input XML Input DTD Output XML Output DTD

        Pre-conditions: This user exit is called conditionally only when deleteCartonContinue method returns false.

        Post-conditions: The return parameter should contain output XML data as required by the removeContainerFromManifest API.


        Parameters:
        env - Required. Environment handle returned by the createEnvironment API. This is required for the user exit to raise errors and access environment information.
        s - Required. For more information, see the associated input xml files.


        NOTE: This user exit can be used to override Connection Parameters for Pierbridge Adaptor.


        Returns:
        An XML document containing input XML data as required by the removeContainerFormManifest API. For details on the output, refer to the associated output files.


        Throws:
        com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSUserExitException - This exception is thrown whenever system errors that the application cannot handle are encountered. The transaction is aborted and changes are rolled back.
